e=[[Tom Cairney]]|sortname=Cairney, Tom|age={{birth date and age|1991|1|20|df=y}}|caps=2|goals=0|club=[[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]|clubnat=ENG|latest={{dts|11 June 2019}}, v. {{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{nat fs break}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=FW|name=[[Lawrence Shankland]]|sortname=Shankland, Lawrence|age={{birth date and age|1995|8|10|df=y}}|caps=2|goals=1|club=[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]|clubnat=SCO|latest={{dts|19 November 2019}}, v. {{fb|KAZ}}}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=FW|name=[[Ryan Fraser]]|sortname=Fraser, Ryan|age={{birth date and age|1994|2|24|df=y}}|caps=11|goals=1|club=[[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]]|clubnat=ENG|latest={{dts|16 November 2019}}, v. {{fb|CYP}}}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=FW|name=[[Johnny Russell (footballer)|Johnny Russell]]|sortname=Russell, Johnny|age={{birth date and age|1990|4|8|df=y}}|caps=14|goals=1|club=[[Sporting Kansas City]]|clubnat=USA|latest={{dts|13 October 2019}}, v. {{fb|SMR}}}}\n{{nat fs r player|no= |pos=FW|name=[[Matt Phillips]]|sortname=Phillips, Matt|age={{birth date and age|1991|3|13|df=y}}|caps=16|goals=1|club=[[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]|clubnat=ENG|latest={{dts|9 September 2019}}, v. {{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{nat fs r player|no= |pos=FW|name=[[Marc McNulty]]|sortname=McNulty, Marc|age={{birth date and age|1992|9|14|df=y}}|caps=2|goals=0|club=[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]|clubnat=SCO|latest={{dts|11 June 2019}}, v. {{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{nat fs break}}\n<sup>RET</sup> Player has announced retirement from international football.<br/>\n{{nat fs end}}\n\n===Honoured players===\nThe [[Scottish Football Association]] operates a [[Scotland national football team roll of honour|roll of honour]] for every player who has made more than 50 appearances for Scotland.<ref name=\"roll of honour\">{{cite web|title=International Roll of Honour |publisher=[[Scottish Football Association]] |url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_football_players.cfm?page=138 |accessdate=9 September 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101011104402/http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_football_players.cfm?page=138 |archivedate=11 October 2010 }}</ref> {{As of|2017|November}} there are 31 members of this roll,<ref name = \"roll of honour\"/> with [[Craig Gordon]] the most recent addition to the list. The qualifying mark of 50 appearances means that many notable Scotland players including [[Jim Baxter]], [[Hughie Gallacher]], [[John Greig]], [[Jimmy Johnstone]], [[Billy McNeill]], [[Bobby Murdoch]], [[Archie Gemmill]] and [[Lawrie Reilly]] are not on the roll of honour.\n\nThe [[Scottish Football Museum]] operates a [[Scottish Football Hall of Fame|hall of fame]] which is open to players and managers involved in [[football in Scotland|Scottish football]]. This means that membership is not restricted to people who have played for Scotland; inductees include [[Brian Laudrup]] and [[Henrik Larsson]]. At the most recent induction ceremony, [[Alan Rough]], [[Martin Buchan]], [[Eddie Gray (footballer, born 1948)|Eddie Gray]], [[Tommy Docherty]], [[Scot Symon]] and [[Bobby Walker (footballer, born 1879)|Bobby Walker]] were added to its membership.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scottish Football Hall of Fame Dinner 2013, Celebrating 10 years of the Scottish Football Hall of Fame|url=http://www.scottishfootballmuseum.org.uk/hall-of-fame/2013.html|work=Scottish Football Museum|accessdate=15 November 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110230226/http://www.scottishfootballmuseum.org.uk/hall-of-fame/2013.html|archivedate=10 November 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Sportscotland]] operates the [[Scottish Sports Hall of Fame]], which has [[Scottish Sports Hall of Fame#Football|inducted some footballers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Sporting legends honoured in Scottish Sports Hall of Fame|url=http://www.sportscotland.org.uk/news/sportscotland/newsarchive/2012/sporting_legends_honoured_in_scottish_sports_hall_of_fame/|accessdate=14 October 2015|publisher=Sportscotland|date=13 October 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304042828/http://www.sportscotland.org.uk/news/sportscotland/newsarchive/2012/sporting_legends_honoured_in_scottish_sports_hall_of_fame/|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Managers==\n{{main|Scotland national football team manager}}\nFrom 1872 to 1953, and 1954 to 1957, the Scotland national team was appointed by a selection committee. [[Andy Beattie]] was manager for six matches in 1954 when Scotland competed at their first World Cup. After the tournament the selection committee resumed their duties, continuing until the appointment of [[Matt Busby]] in 1958. Busby was initially unable to assume his duties due to the serious injuries he sustained in the [[Munich air disaster]].<ref name = \"wsc 1958\"/>\n\nStatistically the most successful manager was [[Alex McLeish]], who won seven of the ten games during his first spell as manager. Discounting managers who took charge of less than ten games, the least successful manager was [[George Burley]], with just three wins in 14 games.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!Name\n!Scotland career\n!Played\n!Won\n!Drawn\n!Lost\n!Win %\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|Selection committee\n|1872\u20131953\n{{WDL|231\n|139\n|42\n|50}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{sortname|Andy|Beattie}}\n|1954\n{{WDL|6\n|2\n|1\n|3}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|Selection committee\n|1954\u20131957\n{{WDL|23\n|10\n|7\n|6}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{sortname|Dawson|Walker}}<ref group=\"note\">Dawson Walker was left in charge of the players due to the Munich air disaster, in which official manager Matt Busby was seriously injured.</ref>\n|1958\n{{WDL|6\n|1\n|2\n|3}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{sortname|Matt|Busby}}\n|1958\n{{WDL|2\n|1\n|1\n|0}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{sortname|Andy|Beattie}}\n|1959\u20131960\n{{WDL|12\n|3\n|3\n|6}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{sortname|Ian|McColl}}\n|1960\u2013